# Hi, I'm Anisah Calvin Cuevas.
<center>
I am a recent UCSB graduate working towards completing the final requirements for a B.A. in Geography with an emphasis in Geographic Information Science. During my short 3 years at UCSB, I found a passion for geography and the role it plays in community health. After I complete my Bachelor's degree, I hope to enter a dual Master's program in Urban Planning and Public Health. With the knowledge gained from my education, I plan to help bring light to the geographic health disparities that surround communities of color.
